title: Kate Middleton in Tiara - Kate Middleton at the China State Banquet
text:
​Right now in London, Kate Middleton is arriving at her first state banquet for the Chinese president. It's not your typical dinner: The dress code for it calls for a formal gown and tiara, ​something Kate has worn only twice since becoming Duchess (the first time was her wedding, the second for a Diplomatic Reception at Buckingham Palace in 2013).
There's been much buzz about what tiara she'll wear, but finally she has revealed her choice:
 First look at Kate at tonight's state banquet in her bespoke Jenny Packham gown, Lovely! https://t.co/A8zd4K73AA pic.twitter.com/1qkA02z3K1
— HELLO! (@hellomag) October 20, 2015
 Duchess of Cambridge heads to tonight's banquet pic.twitter.com/2b99zZq19u
— Mark Stewart (@RegalEyes) October 20, 2015
Look at it, glittering!
Hello! magazine reports Kate appears to be wearing the Lotus Flower tiara:
The Duchess of Cambridge has arrived for her first state banquet at Buckingham Palace! Looks like she's wearing the Lotus Flower tiara.
— HELLO! (@hellomag) October 20, 2015
It's a favorite of Princess Margaret:
Kate, duchess of Cambridge seems to be wearing this tiara tonight. Used to be one of Princess Margaret's favorites. pic.twitter.com/MvZ9myuZ0O
— Marc van der Linden (@MarcvdLinden) October 20, 2015
The dinner hasn't even begun and already KMid has stolen the night.
